## DNS Telemetry Validation

Sysmon Event ID 22 (DNS Query) is confirmed
flowing into Microsoft Sentinel from SOC-DC01,
validated via KQL query extracting QueryName,
Image, and User fields from the raw event
description.

```kql
Event
| where Source == "Microsoft-Windows-Sysmon"
| where EventID == 22
| extend QueryName = extract(@"QueryName: (\S+)", 1, RenderedDescription)
| extend Image = extract(@"Image: (.+?)(?:\r|\n| User:)", 1, RenderedDescription)
| extend User = extract(@"User: (.+?)(?:\r|\n|$)", 1, RenderedDescription)
| project TimeGenerated, QueryName, Image, User
| order by TimeGenerated desc
```

![Sentinel DNS Query Results](screenshots/sentinel-dns-query-results.png)

*DNS query telemetry confirmed in Sentinel — 
showing QueryName, the process that made the 
query, and the user context. This data source 
is critical for detecting C2 beaconing and DNS 
tunneling, since most malware uses DNS to 
communicate with attacker infrastructure.*



